text:
Hi - I have an email template (html) and need 2 (out of 4) of the links in the template to remain white in Outlook.   Can you specifically target 2 of them using &lt;style type="text/css" id="hs-inline-css"&gt;
   a { color: #ffffff; }
&lt;/style&gt;  ?

What Jon said.
So something like below will update your links in the table with an id of `footerTable`:
```
&lt;style type="text/css" data-hse-inline-css="true"&gt;
#footerTable a { color: #ffffff; }
&lt;/style&gt;
```
